{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":true,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"Server-sent events","mdn_url":"/pt-BR/docs/Web/API/Server-sent_events","locale":"pt-BR","native":"Português (do Brasil)","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/pt-BR/docs/Web/API/Server-sent_events\">Server-sent events</a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Guias</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/pt-BR/docs/Web/API/Server-sent_events/Using_server-sent_events\">Using server-sent events</a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Interfaces</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/pt-BR/docs/Web/API/EventSource\"><code>EventSource</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>Traditionally, a web page has to send a request to the server to receive new data; that is, the page requests data from the server. With server-sent events, it's possible for a server to send new data to a web page at any time, by pushing messages to the web page. These incoming messages can be treated as <em><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Event\" class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\">Events (en-US)</a> + data</em> inside the web page.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"concepts_and_usage","title":"Concepts and usage","isH3":false,"content":"<p>To learn how to use server-sent events, see our article <a href=\"/pt-BR/docs/Web/API/Server-sent_events/Using_server-sent_events\">Using server-sent events</a>.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"interfaces","title":"Interfaces","isH3":false,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"eventsource\"><a href=\"/pt-BR/docs/Web/API/EventSource\"><code>EventSource</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Defines all the features that handle connecting to a server, receiving events/data, errors, closing a connection, etc.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"https://github.com/mdn/dom-examples/tree/master/server-sent-events\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Simple SSE demo using PHP</a></li>\n</ul>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"specification","title":"Specification","isH3":false,"content":"<table>\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th>Specification</th>\n      <th>Status</th>\n      <th>Comment</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td><a href=\"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/#server-sent-events\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">HTML Living Standard<br><small lang=\"pt-BR\">The definition of 'Server-sent events' in that specification.</small></a></td>\n      <td><span class=\"spec-living\">Padrão em tempo real</span></td>\n      <td></td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"tools","title":"Tools","isH3":true,"content":"<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"https://github.com/EventSource/eventsource\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">EventSource polyfill for Node.js</a></li>\n  <li>Remy Sharp’s <a href=\"https://github.com/remy/polyfills/blob/master/EventSource.js\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">EventSource polyfill</a></li>\n  <li>Yaffle’s <a href=\"https://github.com/Yaffle/EventSource\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">EventSource polyfill</a></li>\n  <li>Rick Waldron’s <a href=\"https://github.com/rwldrn/jquery.eventsource\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">jquery plugin</a></li>\n  <li>intercooler.js <a href=\"https://intercoolerjs.org/docs.html#sse\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">declarative SSE support</a></li>\n</ul>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"related_topics","title":"Related Topics","isH3":true,"content":"<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"/pt-BR/docs/Web/Guide/AJAX\">AJAX</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/pt-BR/docs/Web/JavaScript\">JavaScript</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/pt-BR/docs/Web/API/WebSockets_API\">WebSockets</a></li>\n</ul>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"other_resources","title":"Other resources","isH3":true,"content":"<ul>\n  <li>A <a href=\"https://hacks.mozilla.org/2011/06/a-wall-powered-by-eventsource-and-server-sent-events/\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Twitter like application</a> powered by server-sent events and <a href=\"https://github.com/mozilla/webowonder-demos/tree/master/demos/friends%20timeline\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">its code on Github</a>.</li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://dsheiko.com/weblog/html5-and-server-sent-events\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">HTML5 and Server-sent events</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://rajudasa.blogspot.in/2012/05/html5-server-sent-events-using-aspnet.html\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Server-sent events using Asp.Net</a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Concepts and usage","id":"concepts_and_usage"},{"text":"Interfaces","id":"interfaces"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specification","id":"specification"},{"text":"See also","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"Traditionally, a web page has to send a request to the server to receive new data; that is, the page requests data from the server. With server-sent events, it's possible for a server to send new data to a web page at any time, by pushing messages to the web page. These incoming messages can be treated as Events (en-US) + data inside the web page.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-10-01T03:41:16.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"Server-sent events","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)"},{"title":"Server-sent events","locale":"es","native":"Español"},{"title":"Server-sent events","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"サーバー送信イベント","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"Server-sent events","locale":"ko","native":"한국어"},{"title":"Server-sent events","locale":"ru","native":"Русский"},{"title":"Server-sent events","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"},{"title":"Server-sent events","locale":"zh-TW","native":"正體中文 (繁體)"}],"source":{"fo